Seven people have been killed in a crash involving a minibus taxi and a truck between Kanyamazane and Mbombela in Mpumalanga on Saturday. All the deceased were in the minibus taxi and include the driver. About 11 people were injured, some seriously injured. They have been taken to various hospitals. Traffic has been disrupted. Mpumalanga Community Safety MEC Pat Ngomane says: “This one involved public transport. Seven people at a go, they died. So it’s very much horrible to us. We wish to communicate to all, specifically drivers of public transport, to obey the rules of the road because they are carrying lives of our people who are many at a time.”   WATCH BELOW: 